space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

1. Sort the input string characters to ensure lexicographical order.
2. Initialize lastChar to the first character of the sorted string.
3. Iterate from the last character to the first character, appending each character to the result string.
4. Return the result string if there are more combinations to return, or return an empty string to indicate the end of combinations.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the input string. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a constant amount of space for the result string. The energy implications are low since the algorithm does not consume significant energy.

